    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>spinach </strong>then add it to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped basil</strong>, <strong>cashew nuts </strong>and <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>blanched peas</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!), <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>green cashew sauce</strong></p>",
